---
description: MoonDB REST API patterns and query syntax
alwaysApply: false
globs: "**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx,py,rb,go,rs}"
---

moondb-api-patterns:

- Base URL pattern: https://api.moondb.ai/p/{project_id}
- CRUD endpoints: GET/POST /api/{table}, GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/{table}/{id}, POST /api/{table}/bulk
- Filter syntax: ?field=op.value (operators: eq, neq, gt, gte, lt, lte, like, in, is_null, not_null)
- Sort: ?sort=field.desc or ?sort=field.asc
- Pagination: ?limit=20&offset=0
- Field selection: ?select=id,name,email
- Include related records: ?include=user_id (expands ref columns)
- List response shape: { data: [...], meta: { total, limit, offset, has_more } }
- Single response shape: { data: { ...row } }
- Error response shape: { error: { code, message, suggestion } }
- Auth endpoints (when auth_table exists): POST /auth/signup, /auth/login, /auth/refresh, GET /auth/me, PATCH /auth/me, POST /auth/logout
- File upload: POST /storage/upload (multipart/form-data with file, table, column, row_id fields)
- AI endpoints: POST /ai/{endpoint_name} { "param": "value" }
